# Toxic Game — Project Overview

Cooperative two-player rhythm game for Raspberry Pi. Python implementation. **Do not start implementation until explicitly requested** — rules and design come first.

## Target Hardware

- **Controller:** Raspberry Pi 3 Model B v1.2 (2025)
- **Inputs:** Two hardware buttons (one per player)
- **Outputs:** Audio playback, WS2811 LED strip
- **Reference prototype:** `/home/pi/rythm-jump` — reuse its GPIO/LED patterns and hardware adapters as the starting point for physical I/O

## Language & Tooling

- **Language:** Python
- **Dependency management:** Prefer `uv` (match prototype conventions where sensible)
- **Physical I/O libraries (from prototype):** `RPi.GPIO` for buttons, `rpi_ws281x` for LED strip
- **Config:** `toxic_game.toml` — single file for all global numeric parameters (hardware + gameplay); per-song `song.toml` under `songs/<id>/`
- **Audio:** pygame mixer (same approach as prototype)

## Players & Cooperation

- Two players, one button each
- **Single shared health pool** — mistakes by either player drain the same health
- Health at 0 → game over

## Out of Scope (for now)

- No web UI unless later specified
- No implementation work unless explicitly requested
